lessons.theory:
## Testing
Go has built-in testing using the `testing` package and `go test`.
```go
func TestAdd(t *testing.T) {
    if add(1,1) != 2 { t.Error("Failed") }
}
```

lessons.starterCode:
package main
import "testing"

func subtract(a, b int) int { return a - b }

func TestSubtract(t *___.___) {
    if subtract(5, 3) != ___ {
        t.___("Expected 2")
    }
}

lessons.solution:
package main
import "testing"
func subtract(a, b int) int { return a - b }
func TestSubtract(t *testing.T) {
    if subtract(5, 3) != 2 {
        t.Errorf("Expected 2")
    }
}
